{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"DE-RISK E2 PASSED (warm-then-fan-out, the S3 load-bearing assumption): (a) COLD concurrent x3 sharing one cached system prompt -> 3 writes / 0 reads (the ~20x all-miss problem is REAL). (b) WARM one call to completion, then concurrent x3 -> 0 writes / 3 reads (all hit). Confirms: parallelize MUST warm first; warm-then-fan-out yields 1 write + (N-1) reads as designed. Threading + run_sync cache reads work correctly."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782559854973273001,"uuid":"0aac2082-6f12-4447-92de-6e6ca6b7e567"}